üì¶ Pitch 1: IBIT Accumulation Program (ASR-Style with Embedded Ceiling)

üß† Strategic Rationale

Bitcoin is entering the later phase of its post-halving cycle, a window that historically has coincided with accelerated institutional inflows and strong price performance. With the Fed expected to begin cutting rates in September, market positioning is shifting toward long-duration and non-sovereign assets. Real rates are beginning to compress, and risk appetite is re-emerging across portfolios.

IBIT has emerged as the preferred institutional wrapper for Bitcoin exposure ‚Äî offering deep liquidity, regulatory clarity, and operational simplicity. For allocators seeking to increase exposure without impacting price, a structured accumulation program offers a capital-efficient, passive approach.

‚∏ª

üîß Trade Structure
	‚Ä¢	Objective: Accumulate a target notional or share count of IBIT over a defined time horizon.
	‚Ä¢	Execution: Passive participation in daily volume, benchmarked to VWAP over a 20‚Äì30 trading day period.
	‚Ä¢	Embedded Ceiling: An optional maximum execution price (e.g. 105% of initial reference level) limits exposure to slippage or breakout risk. If breached intraday, the remaining execution may be deferred or rebalanced.

‚∏ª

üìà Client Benefits
	‚Ä¢	Efficient entry into IBIT over time, minimizing signaling or market impact.
	‚Ä¢	Full transparency via VWAP benchmark execution.
	‚Ä¢	Optional price ceiling provides control over execution slippage in the event of a sharp BTC rally.
	‚Ä¢	Ideal for institutions seeking to position into a potential Q4 risk-on cycle ahead of confirmed Fed cuts.

