üîÑ Pitch 2: IBIT Disposal Program (Reverse ASR-Style with Embedded Floor)

üß† Strategic Rationale

Bitcoin has rallied significantly since the January ETF launches and April 2024 halving. With the first rate cut expected in September, market consensus is increasingly priced in. Some funds may look to rebalance exposure into strength, particularly as crypto beta begins to consolidate post-run. Disposing of a large IBIT position via standard block trades or open market selling risks moving the tape and impacting marks.

A reverse ASR-style structure enables passive, rules-based unwinding with minimal market footprint ‚Äî and can include price protection via an embedded execution floor.

‚∏ª

üîß Trade Structure
	‚Ä¢	Objective: Dispose of a defined IBIT position over a fixed time window.
	‚Ä¢	Execution: Daily participation in market volume, benchmarked to VWAP over 15‚Äì20 trading days.
	‚Ä¢	Embedded Floor: An optional minimum execution price (e.g. 95% of initial reference level) can be embedded. If the floor is breached, execution slows or pauses, with discretion to re-enter as prices recover.

‚∏ª

üìà Client Benefits
	‚Ä¢	Structured, passive disposal of IBIT with reduced market footprint.
	‚Ä¢	Floor-based pricing protection reduces exposure to short-term BTC volatility or macro surprises (e.g. inflation, geopolitics).
	‚Ä¢	Retains full transparency ‚Äî average execution benchmarked to VWAP.
	‚Ä¢	Well-suited for funds seeking to derisk into strength, rotate capital, or tactically reduce BTC beta.

‚∏ª

‚è± Tenor Considerations
	‚Ä¢	15‚Äì20 days: Ideal for tactical disposal programs, allowing risk to be offloaded smoothly over multiple liquidity windows.
	‚Ä¢	20‚Äì30 days: Preferred for strategic accumulation programs, enabling a gradual build into potentially improving macro and crypto market conditions.
